                               Featured Items!
   [FeaturedItemPowerWeb.gif] The ADWR Imaged Records Database Online!
   We're happy to offer the ADWR Imaged Records Database which includes
   Wells 55 Data and much more via a web based access and search tool.
   Requires a small plug-in download.  If you experience trouble accessing
   the ADWR Imaged Records Database, please be sure you are using Internet
   Explorer 4.01 SP 2 or better (5.5 SP2 and 6.x are not supported) or
   Netscape 4.08 or better (6.x is not supported).

   [goldcd.gif] Desert Landscaping Plants For a Water Scarce Environment
   CD-ROM
   Produced by University of Arizonas Water Resources Research Center.
   Contains plant trivia, landscape tips, clickable landscapes,
   interactive plant selector, over 1,500 full-screen photos, reviews of
   two dozen plant books, full information on 600 low water-use plants,
   and pronunciations of common and botanical names.  $25 Buy Now!

   [Featured3rdMgmtPln.gif] Third Management Plans 2000-2010 Softbound
   Books
   Phoenix, Pinal, Prescott, Santa Cruz and Tucson Active Management Areas
   final adoption for years 2000-2010. Purchase of a hard copy entitles
   purchaser to free CD-ROM with all five AMAs included.  Phoenix,
   Prescott, Tucson, Santa Cruz and Pinal. $20
   [AZwaterMapsm.gif] Arizona Water Map
   This map depicts Arizonas water resources accompanied by text and
   photos from The Water Resources Research Center, College of
   Agriculture, The University of Arizona.  This map is suitable for
   framing and classroom use, and features a landforms map of the state
   overlaid with surface water and groundwater features. It contains
   information on vital water issues and color photographs from National
   Geographic and Arizona Highways photographers.  Through color and form,
   the map depicts Arizonas...


